02-nodeselector - Label-Based Scheduling
pod-nodeselector.yaml
Purpose: Schedule pod on nodes with specific labels (GPU example)
File: examples/02-nodeselector/pod-nodeselector.yaml
yamlapiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: gpu-pod
  labels:
    app: ml-training
    method: nodeselector
spec:
  nodeSelector:
    hardware: gpu  # Only schedule on nodes with GPU
  containers:
  - name: tensorflow
    image: tensorflow/tensorflow:latest-gpu
    command: ["python"]
    args: ["-c", "import tensorflow as tf; print('TensorFlow version:', tf.__version__); print('GPU available:', tf.config.list_physical_devices('GPU'))"]
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: "1000m"
        memory: "2Gi"
      limits:
        cpu: "2000m"
        memory: "4Gi"
        nvidia.com/gpu: 1  # Request 1 GPU
Usage:
bash# First label a node with GPU
kubectl label node worker-node-1 hardware=gpu

# Apply the pod
kubectl apply -f examples/02-nodeselector/pod-nodeselector.yaml
kubectl get pod gpu-pod -o wide
Expected Result: Pod scheduled on node with hardware=gpu label

pod-multi-selector.yaml
Purpose: Multiple nodeSelector labels (AND logic)
File: examples/02-nodeselector/pod-multi-selector.yaml
yamlapiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: ssd-high-mem-pod
  labels:
    app: database
    method: nodeselector-multi
spec:
  nodeSelector:
    disktype: ssd    # AND - must have SSD
    memory: high     # AND - must have high memory
  containers:
  - name: postgres
    image: postgres:15
    env:
    - name: POSTGRES_PASSWORD
      value: "mysecretpassword"
    - name: POSTGRES_DB
      value: "production_db"
    ports:
    - containerPort: 5432
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: "500m"
        memory: "1Gi"
      limits:
        cpu: "1000m"
        memory: "2Gi"
    volumeMounts:
    - name: postgres-storage
      mountPath: /var/lib/postgresql/data
  volumes:
  - name: postgres-storage
    emptyDir: {}
Usage:
bash# Label node with both labels
kubectl label node worker-node-1 disktype=ssd memory=high

# Apply pod
kubectl apply -f examples/02-nodeselector/pod-multi-selector.yaml
kubectl get pod ssd-high-mem-pod -o wide
Expected Result: Pod on node with BOTH disktype=ssd AND memory=high

pod-unmatched.yaml
Purpose: Demonstrates pod pending when no nodes match selector
File: examples/02-nodeselector/pod-unmatched.yaml
yamlapiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: nonexistent-label-pod
  labels:
    app: test
    method: nodeselector-unmatched
spec:
  nodeSelector:
    special-hardware: quantum-computer  # This label doesn't exist on any node
  containers:
  - name: nginx
    image: nginx:1.24
    ports:
    - containerPort: 80
    resources:
      requests:
        cpu: "100m"
        memory: "128Mi"
      limits:
        cpu: "200m"
        memory: "256Mi"

# This pod will remain in Pending state because no node has the required label
# Expected error: "0/N nodes are available: N node(s) didn't match Pod's node affinity/selector"
Usage:
bashkubectl apply -f examples/02-nodeselector/pod-unmatched.yaml
kubectl get pod nonexistent-label-pod
kubectl describe pod nonexistent-label-pod | grep -A 5 Events
Expected Result: Pod stuck Pending with error message

deployment-nodeselector.yaml
Purpose: Production deployment with nodeSelector and service
File: examples/02-nodeselector/deployment-nodeselector.yaml
yamlapiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: production-app
  labels:
    app: production-app
    environment: production
spec:
  replicas: 5
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: production-app
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: production-app
        environment: production
    spec:
      nodeSelector:
        environment: production  # Only schedule on production nodes
      containers:
      - name: app
        image: nginx:1.24
        ports:
        - containerPort: 80
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: "250m"
            memory: "256Mi"
          limits:
            cpu: "500m"
            memory: "512Mi"
        livenessProbe:
          httpGet:
            path: /
            port: 80
          initialDelaySeconds: 15
          periodSeconds: 10
        readinessProbe:
          httpGet:
            path: /
            port: 80
          initialDelaySeconds: 5
          periodSeconds: 5
---
apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: production-app-service
spec:
  selector:
    app: production-app
  ports:
  - port: 80
    targetPort: 80
  type: ClusterIP
Usage:
bash# Label production nodes
kubectl label node worker-node-1 environment=production

# Apply deployment
kubectl apply -f examples/02-nodeselector/deployment-nodeselector.yaml
kubectl get pods -l app=production-app -o wide
Expected Result: All 5 replicas on nodes labeled environment=production
